the largest landfill gastoenergy project in georgia republic services converts landfill gas the natural byproduct of decomposing waste to energy the use of landfill gas provides the us economy with benefits including reducing air pollution through the capture and use of methane as of december   republic services operated  landfill gas and renewable energy projects in april  republic services opened a landfill gastoenergy project near los angeles at the sunshine canyon landfill the megawatt renewable energy project has the ability to supply enough electricity to power almost  homes in the area in january  the epas landfill methane outreach program lmop selected three republic services landfill gastoenergy projects lfgte as lfgte projects of the year for  ox mountain landfill in half moon bay california jefferson city landfill in jefferson city missouri and oak grove landfill in winder georgia were honored at the annual lmop conference in baltimore in january  republic services developed lfgte projects at  of its  landfills including  electric generating plants  medium btu plants that provide lfg to industrial users  high btu plants that produce pipeline quality gas and  leachate evaporators the  electric projects generate  mw of electricity enough to power about  homes the  other projects provide or process more than  scfm of gas energy needed to heat almost  homes the combined benefits equivalent to removing about  million cars off the road in  republic services agreed to pay a  million fine and up to  million in remediation costs for alleged violations of the clean water act at a closed landfill in clark county nevada in  republic services was fined  by the state of california related to hazardous waste leaking from a closed landfill into san francisco bay community involvementedit together with memphis habitat for humanity republic services plans to build a rugby field for the gestalt power center academy the field will also be a community resource for new eden sq