ue us billion  operating income us billion  net income us million  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  owner cascade investment  number of employees   website republicservicescom republic services inc is the second largest provider of nonhazardous solid waste collection transfer disposal recycling and energy services in the united states as measured by revenue the company is active in recycling reducing carbon emissions by replacing diesel trucks with compressed natural gas powered trucks supporting composting and other community projects which relate to environmental conservation sustainability and education contents  company history  operations  fleet  renewable natural gas usage  fleet automation  fleet conversion to compressed natural gas cng  landfills  regulation  customer service  corporate responsibility sustainability and innovation  recycling  composting  landfill gas to energy lfgte  community involvement  awards and recognition  lobbying  references  external links company historyedit republic industries was created as a waste disposal firm in  h wayne huizenga became chairman of the board in  at that time republic industries began acquiring auto dealerships and car rental agencies in  republic industries spun off republic services as an ipo then changed its name to autonation in june  republic became the second largest waste management company in the us following the acquisition of its larger competitor allied waste industries for  billion in republic stock the merged company retained the republic services name the wall street journal reported in june  that republic services’  billion acquisition of allied in december  has been successful from the start delivering at the high end of the annual savings projected when they did the deal  million a  increase in share price after  years as ceo of republic services james o’connor retired on january   replacing him was the president and coo of republic services donald slager thomas w handley and jennifer m kirk were appointed to the republic services board of directors at the end of july  expanding the number of board members to   of them independent operationsedit republic services’ operations primarily consist of providing collection transfer and disposal of nonhazardous solid waste recovering and recycling of certain materials and energy services as of december   it operated in  states and puerto rico through  collection operations  transfer stations  active landfills  recycling centers  treatment recovery and disposal facilities and  salt water disposal wells republic also operated  landfill gas and renewable energy projects and had postclosure responsibility for  closed landfills in january  republic realigned its field support functions by combining its three regions into two field groups consolidating its areas and streamlining select operational support roles at its phoenix headquarters fleetedit according to fleet owner   republic services ranked  in the us in total number of trucks in service with  renewable natural gas usageedit republic services announced in may  that it will increase its usage of renewable natural gas rng by a factor of three above what it used in  they will also reduce usage of coe carbon dioxide equivalent by about  metric tons by their fleet over the coming three years with an expanded agreement with clean energy  fleet automationedit approximately  of its residential routes have been converted to automated single driver trucks by converting its residential routes to automated service they reduce labor costs improve driver productivity decrease emissions and create a safer work environment for its employees additionally communities using automated vehicles have higher participation rates in recycling programs thereby complementing its initiative to expand its recycling capabilities fleet conversion to compressed natural gas cngedit as of november  republic services operated a fleet of almost  cngpowered vehicles supported by  natural gas fueling stations according to the company their cng fleet helped to save about  million gallons of diesel fuel in august  republic services opened a new compressed natural gas cng fueling station in long beach california the station will serve the recent addition of  cngpowered garbage trucks which replaced their old diesel trucks with this addition of cng trucks the total number of alternative fuel vehicles operating in long beach is  in broward and dade counties in south florida republic services added  cng trucks to their collection fleet in april  the addition brought the total number of trucks to  on earth day april   republic services announced enhancements they made to the anaheim recycling center the new system was designed by rrt design  construction and bulk handling systems the new system can handle over  tons of recyclables each day or  tons per hour in central contra costa county republic services added  compressed natural gas solid waste collection trucks to its fleet the cng trucks replaced dieselpowered garbage collection trucks as of april  the total number of cng trucks operated by republic in contra costa county was  in portland republic services added  cng solid waste collection trucks to its fleet in april  in st louis the company added four cng solid waste collection trucks to its fleet bringing the total number of cng trucks in the region to  at the end of  republic services opened a  million  squarefoot recycling center in north las vegas the plant is stateoftheart with rooftop solar panels generating enough energy to run the plant for two to three months the plant is designed to process one million pounds of recycled paper each day going up to two million pounds as automation is completed during the coming three years eventually the plant will be able to recycle three million pounds of paper per day approximately  of its fleet operates on cng approximately  of its replacement vehicle purchases during  were cng vehicles as of de